impossible to find consistency in the naming process. Confucius had stressed that correct names make for the best relationships. In this case, Professor Leo Suryadinata has been pursuing for decades the elusive goal of finding the right name to give to the large numbers of people who have, in one way or another, made their homes in, or made some difference to, Southeast Asia. I believe that, when he and his colleagues selected the biographies to be included here, they have taken a big step towards the rectification of identities for many leading personalities. In so doing, he has done us all a great service.” - Professor Wang Gungwu, National University of Singapore  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChinesezSoutheast AsiavBiographyvDictionaries. 0aChinese--Southeast Asia--Biography--Dictionaries. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aGungwu, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuryadinata, Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuryadinata, Leo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106066830 cprintz978981434521740uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981434522440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814345224423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789814345224/original  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (200